{
  "stem": "353.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were waiting until something that we got to eat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "After work, we got some soup, some-- a piece of bread, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was in this concentration camp, Plaszow, until [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my brother, the youngest brother-- factory closed up, and all Jews from this factory came out to-- to Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my youngest brother came with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And a few days later, he was [GERMAN] again to a vernichtungslagers, others, like Belzec, like other-- other camps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure, we knew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew-- then, we knew everything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then-- then they--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was-- this was in March, 1940-- March-- between March and May, 1943, when-- when the ghetto was liquidated, we already knew that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I jumped the train, I already knew that this-- this train, those people who were in this train, didn't go to-- to work.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Only went right straight into oven.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And probably half of them were dead already in the cars.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in 19-- 1943, in Plaszow, I was working as an electrician.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I changed my trade.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Before, I was an auto mechanic, then I was electrician.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I would-- I was working electrician.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was wearing a belt, all kind of tools around.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I had the permission to walk around the camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If somebody stopped me, I was electrician, go fix the wires, electric wires, this and that.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
